Plug-in name: Instantiate
Plug-in shortname: instantiate
Description: Overrides standard library functions

Most options of the form '-instantiate-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-instantiate-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-instantiate         (opposite option is -no-instantiate)
-instantiate-calloc  Activate replacement for function 'calloc' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-calloc)
-instantiate-fct <f,...>  Override stdlib functions only into the specified
                    functions (defaults to all). (preferably use
                    -instantiate-fct="f,...")
-instantiate-free   Activate replacement for function 'free' (set by default,
                    opposite option is -instantiate-no-free)
-instantiate-malloc  Activate replacement for function 'malloc' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-malloc)
-instantiate-memcmp  Activate replacement for function 'memcmp' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-memcmp)
-instantiate-memcpy  Activate replacement for function 'memcpy' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-memcpy)
-instantiate-memmove  Activate replacement for function 'memmove' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-memmove)
-instantiate-memset  Activate replacement for function 'memset' (set by
                    default, opposite option is -instantiate-no-memset)

*** DEBUG

-instantiate-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in Instantiate (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-instantiate-help   help of plug-in Instantiate
-instantiate-h      alias for option -instantiate-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-instantiate-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Instantiate to a
                    file. <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -instantiate-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-instantiate-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -instantiate-msg-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories (preferably use
                    -instantiate-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-instantiate-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Instantiate (default
                    to 1)
-instantiate-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for
                    category <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use
                    -instantiate-warn-key help to get a list of available
                    categories, and * to enable all categories. Possible
                    statuses are inactive, feedback, warning, error, abort,
                    feedback-once, warning-once, error-once. Defaults to
                    warning. (preferably use
                    -instantiate-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
